about.summary: Collection of plotting and table output functions for data visualization. Results of various statistical analyses (that are commonly used in social sciences) can be visualized using this package, including simple and cross tabulated frequencies, histograms, box plots, (generalized) linear models, mixed effects models, principal component analysis and correlation matrices, cluster analyses, scatter plots, stacked scales, effects plots of regression models (including interaction terms) and much more. This package supports labelled data.

name: r-sjplot
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "2.8.15" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-sjplot
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/sjPlot_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/sjPlot/sjPlot_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 5a760859243fee2f63cda3711d23d15bfe29f9170db87ad595f24e661bb29b82

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-mass
    - r-bayestestr
    - r-datawizard
    - r-dplyr
    - r-effectsize
    - r-ggeffects
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.2.0
    - r-insight
    - r-knitr
    - r-parameters
    - r-performance
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-scales
    - r-sjlabelled >=1.1.2
    - r-sjmisc >=2.8.2
    - r-sjstats >=0.17.8
    - r-tidyr >=1.0.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-mass
    - r-bayestestr
    - r-datawizard
    - r-dplyr
    - r-effectsize
    - r-ggeffects
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.2.0
    - r-insight
    - r-knitr
    - r-parameters
    - r-performance
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-scales
    - r-sjlabelled >=1.1.2
    - r-sjmisc >=2.8.2
    - r-sjstats >=0.17.8
    - r-tidyr >=1.0.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('sjPlot')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('sjPlot')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://strengejacke.github.io/sjPlot/
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: Collection of plotting and table output functions for data visualization. Results of various statistical analyses (that are commonly used in social sciences) can be visualized using this package, including simple and cross tabulated frequencies, histograms, box plots, (generalized) linear models, mixed effects
    models, principal component analysis and correlation matrices, cluster analyses, scatter plots, stacked scales, effects plots of regression models (including interaction terms) and much more. This package supports labelled data.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - ccwang002
